  "text": "CDH17, as other cadherins, is a target for ectodomain shedding because of the presence of elevated protease activity in the tumor microenvironment. Previous observations confirmed the shedding of CDH17 in the conditioned medium of KM12SM cells [CITATION_1] . The secreted soluble form of CDH17 contained the RGD domain. This shedding in metastatic cells makes CDH17 a candidate biomarker for detection in biofluids (serum or plasma) of colon cancer patients. Therefore, CDH17 could be useful for patient stratification and targeted therapy.",
